TY  - JOUR
AU  - Lapan, Harvey E.
AU  - Enders, Walter
T1  - Rational Expectations, Endogenous Currency Substitution, and Exchange Rate Determination*
PY  - 1983
Y1  - 1983/08/01
DO  - 10.2307/1886019
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 98
IS  - 3
SP  - 427
EP  - 439
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The paper employs the intergenerational model to derive the demands for domestic and foreign currencies from microeconomic optimizing behavior. In the absence of government policy, we obtain the Kareken and Wallace result that exchange rates are constant and indeterminate. We discuss the reasons why nations may find it in their interests to impose probabilistic capital controls. It is shown that the imposition of probabilistic capital controls yields a unique (generally nonstationary) exchange rate path and that this path is determined in accord with the Monetary Approach. As the probability of controls tends to zero, the exchange rate remains determinate.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1886019
ER  - 



