TY  - JOUR
AU  - Becker, Gary S.
T1  - A Theory of Competition Among Pressure Groups for Political Influence*
PY  - 1983
Y1  - 1983/08/01
DO  - 10.2307/1886017
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 98
IS  - 3
SP  - 371
EP  - 400
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper presents a theory of competition among pressure groups for political influence. Political equilibrium depends on the efficiency of each group in producing pressure, the effect of additional pressure on their influence, the number of persons in different groups, and the deadweight cost of taxes and subsidies. An increase in deadweight costs discourages pressure by subsidized groups and encourages pressure by taxpayers. This analysis unifies the view that governments correct market failures with the view that they favor the politically powerful: both are produced by the competition for political favors.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1886017
ER  - 



